## 19. DESIGN SYSTEM — USE THESE TOKENS EVERYWHERE

### Colours (define in Colors.swift as static extensions on Color)
```swift
// Backgrounds
Color.bg.primary      = #0A0A0F   // OLED black — main background
Color.bg.secondary    = #0E0E1E   // Cards, sheets
Color.bg.tertiary     = #12122A   // Elevated surfaces

// Accent
Color.accent.primary  = #6C63FF   // Brand colour, XP bars, CTAs, active tab glow
Color.accent.secondary = #A78BFA  // Headings, secondary highlights
Color.accent.gold     = #F59E0B   // Rank S+, golden crown, elite achievements
Color.accent.electric = #3B82F6   // Electric blue (app icon accent, links)

// Status
Color.status.danger   = #EF4444   // Punishments, violations, failures
Color.status.success  = #22C55E   // Completions, rewards
Color.status.warning  = #F97316   // Warnings, deadlines approaching

// Text
Color.text.primary    = #E2E8F0   // Main text
Color.text.secondary  = #94A3B8   // Secondary text, labels
Color.text.muted      = #64748B   // Timestamps, metadata

// Rank colours
Color.rank.E = #4B5563 | Color.rank.D = #1D4ED8 | Color.rank.C = #7C3AED
Color.rank.B = #6D28D9 | Color.rank.A = #4C1D95 | Color.rank.S = #F59E0B
Color.rank.SS = #D97706 | Color.rank.SSS = #6C63FF (animated)
```

### Typography (define in Typography.swift)
```swift
// Always use these, never hardcode font sizes
Font.vigil.display     = SF Pro Rounded, 48pt, Black weight    // Rank on rank card
Font.vigil.titleLarge  = SF Pro Display, 34pt, Bold            // Screen titles
Font.vigil.title       = SF Pro Display, 28pt, Semibold        // Section headers
Font.vigil.headline    = SF Pro Text, 17pt, Semibold           // Card titles
Font.vigil.body        = SF Pro Text, 15pt, Regular            // Descriptions
Font.vigil.caption     = SF Mono, 12pt, Regular                // XP numbers, timestamps
Font.vigil.system      = SF Mono, 14pt, Medium                 // ALL AI-generated text
// NO Dynamic Type — VIGIL controls its own typography
// Use .fixedSize() where needed to prevent system font scaling
```

### Spacing (define in Spacing.swift)
```swift
Spacing.xs  = 4pt
Spacing.sm  = 8pt
Spacing.md  = 16pt
Spacing.lg  = 24pt
Spacing.xl  = 32pt
Spacing.xxl = 48pt
```

---

## 20. LOADING STATES

All loading states use the same component: `VIGILLoadingView`
- Pulsing VIGIL eye icon (accent.primary colour)
- Optional message below in SF Mono: "System processing..." etc.
- Never use ProgressView() default iOS spinner anywhere in the app
- Performance targets:
  - All local SwiftData operations: < 300ms
  - AI Foundation Models processing: < 2 seconds (show VIGILLoadingView)
  - Swift Charts rendering: < 500ms

---

## 21. NOTIFICATIONS — ALL COPY DEFINED HERE

All notification copy lives in `NotificationContent.swift`. Never hardcode strings elsewhere.

| Type | Title | Body |
|---|---|---|
| Morning Brief | "VIGIL" | AI-generated (max 3 sentences) |
| Quest Issued | "New Assignment" | "A quest has been assigned. You have [N] hours." |
| Deadline Warning | "Clock Running" | "[Quest title]. Time is running out." |
| Block Violation | "Violation Detected" | "Discipline XP deducted. The system has noted this." |
| Daily Reset | "New Day" | "A new day has begun. The system is watching." |
| Punishment | "System Judgement" | "The system has rendered judgement." |
| Streak Milestone | "Noted" | "Day [N] complete. The system has noted this." |
| Inactivity | "Absence Noted" | "18 hours of silence. The system does not wait." |

User can toggle each type independently in Settings (NotificationManager reads these flags before scheduling)

---

## 22. WIDGET SPECIFICATIONS

**Medium Home Screen Widget:**
- Left side: Rank card mini (rank badge, username, active title)
- Right side: 3 active goals with progress bars
- Background: bg.secondary with subtle accent border
- Updates: WidgetKit timeline, every 15 minutes + on significant events

**Lock Screen Widget:**
- Shows: active quest title + deadline countdown
- If no active quest: shows perfectDayStreak count
- Circular or rectangular accessory widget (both sizes)

**Dynamic Island:**
- When timer running: live countdown of current session (takes priority)
- When no timer + active quest: quest deadline countdown
- When no timer + no quest: shows today's discipline score
- Implementation: ActivityKit Live Activity

---

## 23. SIRI INTEGRATION

App Intent: `StartFocusSessionIntent`
- Phrase: "Hey Siri, start a focus session in VIGIL"
- Behavior: opens app, starts focus timer for most recent/highest priority goal
- If multiple goals: Siri asks "Which goal?" and shows list

---

## 24. iOS FOCUS MODE INTEGRATION

- Starting any in-app timer → automatically enables a VIGIL-created Focus Mode called "VIGIL: Active"
- This Focus Mode silences all notifications except VIGIL notifications
- Timer stops → Focus Mode deactivates
- Implementation: `FocusModeManager.swift` using `FocusFilterIntent`

---

## 25. SYSTEM LOG

Tab structure inside Profile → System Log:
- Filter pills at top: ALL | VERDICTS | PUNISHMENTS | REWARDS | QUESTS
- Chronological within each filter, newest first
- Events logged: XP gains/losses with reason, titles awarded/stripped, rank changes, AI verdicts
- Entry tap: pushes to full detail view (LogEntryDetailView)
- Never delete log entries — permanent record

---

## 26. PROFILE STRUCTURE

ProfileView contains a List of sections:
1. Stats → pushes to StatsOverviewView
2. Goals → pushes to GoalListView
3. System Log → pushes to SystemLogView
4. Settings → pushes to SettingsView

At top of ProfileView:
- Mini rank card (tappable → expands to shareable full rank card)
- Share options: export as image card OR generate public profile link
- Golden crown indicator visible if hasGoldenCrown = true
- "Unawakened" tag visible if hasUnawokenTag = true

---

## 27. STATS SCREEN

Landing: StatsOverviewView
- All 4 stats as overview cards (tap any → deep dive)
- Overview shows: current level, current XP, week graph (7-day mini chart)
- Discipline card rendered slightly larger (master stat emphasis)

Deep dive per stat (StatDeepDiveView):
- Time range picker: 7D | 30D | 90D | 1Y
- XP line graph (Swift Charts)
- Heatmap (GitHub-style, each day a coloured square, intensity = performance score)
- Goal breakdown (which goals fed this stat, pie or bar chart)
- AI written insight (weekly paragraph from Foundation Models, SF Mono font)
- Best day / worst day cards

---

## 28. DAILY/WEEKLY/MONTHLY REVIEW SCHEDULE

- **Daily reset**: wakeTime - 30 minutes. Background task.
- **Morning brief**: at wakeTime. Notification + in-app brief on first open.
- **Weekly review**: every Sunday at 10pm local time. Visual scorecard + 1-sentence AI verdict.
- **Monthly review**: last day of month at 10pm. AI trend analysis + difficulty recalibration.

Weekly review format: StatScorecard view (grades per stat A–F) + single cold AI sentence
Monthly review format: VerdictOverlayView with extended AI analysis (paragraph) + pattern highlights

---

## 29. DATA BACKUP & SOCIAL PREP

**Phase 1:**
- iCloud CloudKit: automatic, seamless, no user action
- Full restore on new device: all Player data, goals, logs, verdicts restored
- New device: must re-sign contract (ContractView shown again), all data populates

**Analytics:**
- Opt-in only (asked in Settings)
- Anonymous only — no PII ever leaves device
- If opted in: anonymised stat patterns sent to improve AI prompts

**Phase 2 social prep (data model ready now):**
- Player.friendCode: 6-character alphanumeric, generated at onboarding
- Player.supabaseUserId: nil in Phase 1, populated in Phase 2
- Friend discovery: friend codes + Apple contacts + username search (all three)
- DO NOT implement Supabase in Phase 1. Scaffold the Social folder. Leave SocialPlaceholder.swift.

---

## 30. PERMISSIONS HANDLING

**Request order (on PermissionsView — Screen 10 of onboarding):**
1. Notifications (UserNotifications) — show in-character explanation first
2. HealthKit (HKHealthStore) — show in-character explanation first
3. FamilyControls (Screen Time) — show in-character explanation first

**In-character explanation template:**
"The system requires [permission] to observe you. Without it, [specific consequence]. Grant access to maintain full system function."

**If permission denied:**
- App continues to dashboard — never block
- Reduced capacity banner persists: "VIGIL is operating at reduced capacity. Grant access to restore full function."
- Banner taps open iOS Settings deep link for that specific permission

---

## 31. ACCESSIBILITY

- VoiceOver: minimum labels on all interactive elements (enough to pass App Review)
- Dynamic Type: NOT supported — VIGIL uses fixed typography, use `.fixedSize()` where needed
- Reduce Motion: ALWAYS respected — check `UIAccessibility.isReduceMotionEnabled` before playing animations
- Reduce Motion alternative: `.opacity` fade transitions replace all motion animations
- Minimum tap target: 44×44pt on all interactive elements

---

## 32. GOAL CREATION (CONVERSATIONAL AI FLOW)

GoalCreateView uses Foundation Models in a conversational mode:
1. AI asks: "What do you want to track?"
2. User types natural language answer: "I want to limit pool to 1 hour"
3. AI parses intent and fills: name="Pool", category=.discipline, type=.duration, targetValue=60, isCapGoal=true
4. Preview card shows parsed goal — user confirms or edits individual fields
5. User selects start date
6. Goal created and activated on start date

AI parsing prompt must extract: name, category, goalType, targetValue, unit, isCapGoal
If AI cannot parse: show manual form with all fields

---

## 33. WHAT NEVER TO DO

- NEVER use third-party chart libraries — Swift Charts only
- NEVER write back to HealthKit
- NEVER add Supabase in Phase 1
- NEVER use UserDefaults for model data — SwiftData only
- NEVER use NavigationLink for verdict/overlay screens — use ZStack overlay
- NEVER hardcode colours or font sizes — always use design tokens
- NEVER use default iOS ProgressView spinner
- NEVER show warm/encouraging empty states — always cold and in-character
- NEVER use exclamation marks in any AI-generated or system copy
- NEVER let the AI personality deviate from cold/authoritative
- NEVER implement Spotlight Search indexing
- NEVER request permissions without showing in-character explanation first
- NEVER use light mode as default — dark is always default
- NEVER implement Apple Watch in Phase 1
- NEVER delete System Log entries
- NEVER show the Awakening Quest alongside other quests — it gates the system

---

## 34. SWIFT CODING CONVENTIONS

- Use `@Observable` (Swift 5.9+) for ViewModels — NOT `ObservableObject`
- Use Swift concurrency (`async/await`) everywhere — NO Combine
- Use `@MainActor` on all ViewModels
- Errors: define typed error enums per feature — no bare `Error` throws
- Constants: define in relevant feature namespace, not as global vars
- All magic strings in dedicated constants files
- All AI prompt templates in `PromptEngine.swift` — never inline prompts in views
- Background tasks: use `BGTaskScheduler` for daily reset and pattern analysis
- File length: if a file exceeds 300 lines, split it

